reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 19, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A great projector...for certain uses.
reviews.reviewText: There a bit of misinformation. This is a “WiFi” projector in that it connects to WiFi for updates, and a limited gamut of apps usable by its android operating system. It does NOT allow WiFi screen casting through miracast without a WiFi enabled dongle which connects through the HDMI port.There’s no way use miracast as an input source, you only have the three options of hardware input ports: VGA, HDMI and USB. So it’s not truly WiFi enabled.It’s also not truly Bluetooth enabled. Now to be fair, I only wanted the WiFi for a sound bar connection, so for me it’s working great. But it will not connect to a mobile device (at least I’ve not been able to sort that one out.)It’s also nowhere close to 7300 lumens. It might be 4000. It’s pretty bright, but not 7000+ bright.With the misinformation aside, this is a fantastic projector for the money, and depending on what you need it for, it will serve you well. Assuming the bulb lasts, since I can’t seem to open it, it should be a great projector for a long time. I’m super excited to use it. It’s got a crisp picture, and vivid color. That’s also compared to the BenQ and epson projectors we use at our church.Other small annoyances FYI:You have to peel the feet off to get at the mounting holes, and there is a power toggle AND a button. Weird.Overall, great for the money! I’m a happy customer! 4/5

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Does not work on BLUETOOTH for iPhone / Apple products
reviews.reviewText: We love lots about this projector, BUT the most important thing - bluetoothing it to our iPhone, iPad, MacBook - which is claimed it could do in the pictures diagram - hasn’t proved possible.Would love some help in this regard if we are to change our review. We are considering buying an Apple TV as we believe this may help. But needing to buy an external device would have been helpful before choosing this projector.Update: The company got back to me and said it does not have bluetooth capability EXCEPT to an external speaker. They apologized and said they updated the product listing to make sure it was more clear for everyone in the future. They are accepting my return (as this aspect of bluetooth was important to me) and I can't ask for anything more! While this wasn't the projector for me it could be for you. It was very bright and had a nice look to the picture we enjoyed. I didn't love the little buzz that came along with this projector (and I think is common in projectors) but I'm a music producer who has pretty sensitive ears. All and all seems like a good company with a good product. Just not for me :)
